 Substances\nBULLET::::- List of inorganic compounds\nBULLET::::- List of organic compounds\nBULLET::::- List of alkanes\nBULLET::::- List of alloys\n\nBULLET::::- Other\nBULLET::::- List of thermal conductivities\nBULLET::::- List of purification methods in chemistry\nBULLET::::- List of unsolved problems in chemistry\n\nBULLET::::- Outline of biochemistry\nBULLET::::- Outline of physics\n\nBULLET::::- International Union of Pure and Applied Chemistry\nBULLET::::- IUPAC Nomenclature Home Page, see especially the \"Gold Book\" containing definitions of standard chemical terms\nBULLET::::- Interactive Mind Map of Chemistry\nBULLET::::- / Chemical energetics\n"}
{"id": "6901", "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki?curid=6901", "title": "Outline of critical theory", "text": "Outline of critical theory\n\nThe following outline is provided as an overview of and topical guide to critical theory:\n\nCritical theory – the examination and critique of society and culture, drawing from knowledge across the social sciences and humanities. The term has two different meanings with different origins and histories: one originating in sociology and the other in literary criticism. This has led to the very literal use of 'critical theory' as an umbrella term to describe any theory founded upon critique.\n\nBULLET::::- Cultural studies –\nBULLET::::- Critical theorists –\nBULLET::::- Works in critical theory –\nBULLET::::- Truth theory –\n\nBULLET::::- Social theory –\nBULLET::::- Literary theory –\nBULLET::::- Thing theory –\nBULLET::::- Critical theory of technology –\nBULLET::::- Critical legal studies –\n\nAfrican-American Theory\nBULLET::::- Henry Louis Gates Jr. –\n\nGender studies\nBULLET::::- Lauren Berlant –\nBULLET::::- Judith Butler –\nBULLET::::- Raewyn Connell –\nBULLET::::- Susan McClary –\nBULLET::::- Laura Mulvey –\n\nMarxist philosophy\nBULLET::::- Frankfurt School –\nBULLET::::- Theodor Adorno –\nBULLET::::- Herbert Marcuse –\nBULLET::::- Walter Benjamin –\nBULLET::::- Jürgen Habermas –\nBULLET::::- Max Horkheimer –\nBULLET::::- Friedrich Pollock –\nBULLET::::- Louis Althusser –\nBULLET::::- Mikhail Bakhtin –\nBULLET::::- Étienne Balibar –\nBULLET::::- Ernst Bloch –\nBULLET::::- Antonio Gramsci –\nBULLET::::- Michael Hardt –\nBULLET::::- Fredric Jameson –\nBULLET::::- Ernesto Laclau –\nBULLET::::- Georg Lukács –\nBULLET::::- Chantal Mouffe –\nBULLET::::- Antonio Negri –\nBULLET::::- Valentin Voloshinov –\nBULLET::::- Slavoj Žižek –\nBULLET::::- Hegemony –\nBULLET::::- Posthegemony –\n\nPostcolonialism\nBULLET::::- Chinua Achebe –\nBULLET::::- \"An Image of Africa\" –\nBULLET::::- Homi Bhabha –\nBULLET::::- Frantz Fanon –\n