{"id": "6982", "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki?curid=6982", "title": "List of classical music competitions", "text": "List of classical music competitions\n\nEuropean Classical music has long relied on music competitions to provide a public forum that identifies the strongest players and contributes to the establishment of their professional careers. This is a list of current competitions in classical music, with each competition and reference link given only once. Many offer competitions across a range of categories and in these cases they are listed under \"General/mixed\". Competitions with age restrictions are listed under \"Young musicians\".\n\nBULLET::::- Bucharest International Music Competition  Wind Quintet & Brass Quintet\nBULLET::::- Classic Pure Vienna International Music Competitions (Vienna, Austria)\nBULLET::::- International Michael-Haydn-Competition Salzburg (Salzburg, Austria)\nBULLET::::- Chesapeake Chamber Music Competition (Maryland, US)\nBULLET::::- Classic Pure Vienna International Music Competitions (Vienna, Austria)\nBULLET::::- International Michael-Haydn-Competition Salzburg (Salzburg, Austria)\nBULLET::::- Duo Entendre Composition Competition for French horn and piano (Newcastle, Australia)\nBULLET::::- Henri Tomasi International Woodwind Quintet Competition (Marseille, France)\nBULLET::::- Malta International Chamber Music Competition, Valletta/Mdina, Malta\nBULLET::::- International Chamber Music Competition Città di Pinerolo e Torino Città metropolitana (Pinerolo, Italy)\nBULLET::::- International Chamber Music Competition Hamburg for piano trios and string quartets (Hamburg, Germany)\nBULLET::::- International Chamber Music Ensemble Competition of New England (Boston, Massachusetts, US)\nBULLET::::- International Contest–Festival of Chamber Ensemble Performance (Magnitogorsk, Russia)\nBULLET::::- International FEURICH Competition for Piano, Voice and Chamber Music (Vienna, Austria)\nBULLET::::- International Maria Yudina Compet